body:
@nikoststs yes several people have asked for this, but it is quite complicated. Each new detection would need to compare to all current trackIDs using some sort of metric function for similarity (possibly using it's latest feature vector), and assigned to an existing track or added to a new track ID.
Kalman filters are often used for this.

There are actually entire detection architecture dedicated to this, so it is not a simple change. Deepsort comes to mind.
